<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="767">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182088" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole triplex Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole triplex Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplex">Pheidole triplex</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="767">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="767">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182088" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole triplex Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole triplex Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplex">triplex</taxonomicName>
, three parts, referring to the tricolorous condition of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="767">
Diagnosis Major: virtually identical with 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata major</taxonomicName>
except for its much smaller size (HW about 0.8 mm versus more than 0.9 mm in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
) and strikingly different color (see below). Stefan Cover, who has examined this species and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
in detail, reports that the head of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182088" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole triplex Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole triplex Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplex">triplex major</taxonomicName>
is also slightly narrower.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="767">
Minor: virtually identical with 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
minor except for its strikingly different color (see below). Another possible difference is habitat: the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182088" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole triplex Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole triplex Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplex">triplex</taxonomicName>
types were collected in mature mountain rainforest, while 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34032" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subarmata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="767" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarmata">subarmata</taxonomicName>
prefers open, even disturbed habitats. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.80, HL 1.06, SL 0.44, EL 0.12, PW 0.46. Paratype minor: HW 0.42, HL 0.46, SL 0.42, EL 0.09, PW 0.28.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="767">Color Major: strongly tricolorous, with head and mandibles uniformly medium brown; mesosoma, waist, and appendages yellow;</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="767">and gaster light brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="767">Minor: concolorous clear light yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="767">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="767">Biology The type colony was found in mature montane rainforest, nesting beneath a rock in clay soil. A seed cache was present.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph>Type locality TRINIDAD: Aripo Ridge, Arima Valley, 550-650 m (Stefan Cover and Mark W. Moffett). [Not figured]</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
